Date: Thu 14 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: FoxSports.news.com [edited]
<http://foxsports.news.com.au/story/0,8659,10139256-2,00.html>

Footy great is among 8 people infected by flesh-eating bacteria
-----------------------------------------------
Doctors are investigating 8 cases of infection by the mysterious
_Mycobacterium ulcerans_ or Bairnsdale ulcer. The latest outbreak of the
disease, which eats away skin, flesh, and fat has again been linked to
Victoria's Bellarine Peninsula. [Although the infection is locally erosive
to the tissues, it does not cause necrotizing fasciitis, the so-called
flesh-eating disease - Mod.LL]
Victoria's chief health officer, Dr. Robert Hall, confirmed that 6 of the 8
victims lived in, or had stayed at, Point Lonsdale. Authorities know the
Bairnsdale ulcer is related to tuberculosis and leprosy, but are unsure
about how it is transmitted to humans.
One of those afflicted is a well-known Australian footballer, who is a
former Hawthorn and Carlton premiership coach. He became infected in a
wound behind his knee.
[Byline: Paula Beauchamp]
